# Dev Notes changelist

The title screen shows a **Dev Notes** tag (top-right) backed by `packages/ui/src/devNotes.ts`.
Players/testers read it to see what changed in the build they're running, and **scroll** through
older builds in the panel.

## On every commit + push to GitHub

Update `packages/ui/src/devNotes.ts`:

- **Always prepend** a new `DevNote` at `DEV_NOTES[0]` (newest first). Never replace, delete, or
  merge bullets into an existing entry — each push is its own version in the scrollable list.
- Give every entry a unique `id` (e.g. `'2026-07-01-summit-switchback'`). Same-day pushes are fine.
- Set `date` to today's ISO date, a one-line `title`, and short **player-facing** `changes` bullets
  for **this build only** (what changed, not how).
- Keep older entries below the new one so history accumulates.
- The newest entry's `date` is the visible build stamp (`DEV_BUILD`) — keep it accurate.

Keep it terse and user-facing. This is separate from `docs/CHANGELOG-KNOWLEDGE.md` (team/knowledge
relay); a change isn't done until both the knowledge base and, when shipping, the Dev Notes reflect it.
